## Synopsis
Practical 3 of Fundamentals of Programming COMP1005/5005

## Contents
README – readme file for Practical 3
growthplot.py - simulation of unconstrained growth using lists to store data to plot
numbersarray.py - Read ten numbers give sum, min, max & mean
growtharray.py - simulation of unconstrained growth using arrays to store data to plot
growthsubplot.py - simulation of unconstrained growth using arrays to store data to subplots
numbersbar.py - Read ten numbers give sum, min, max & mean and plot a bar chart
dosage.py - simulates the amount of aspirin in the system
repeatdosage.py - Simulation of repeated asprin dosages
rainbows.py - Simulation of rainbow with arrays and matplotlib
venv - Python Virtual Environment

## Dependencies
matplotlib - for ploting purposes
numpy - for arrays
venv - Python venv has used for virtual environment

## Version information
2026 Mar 27 - initial version of Practical 3 programs
